`ISuggestion` [`filterText`](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/master/src/vs/editor/common/modes.ts#L215) is not easy to use. One of the reasons is the fact that the accepted suggestion has to be longer than the `filterText`.
Due to this I had to fall back to using `incomplete: true` suggestions.
In order to repro just change `incomplete: false` [here](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/master/src/vs/workbench/parts/debug/electron-browser/repl.ts#L191) and debug the following code:

```
var o = {};
o['hello world'] = 123;
debugger;
```
